						               													<description>The theme of this game is based on the famous book by Robert Louis Stevenson, where he tells the story of the good Dr. Jekyll, who drank a mysterious potion that turned him into the evil Mr. Hyde.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has 8 characters Jekyll / Hyde. All figures show on the front Dr. Jekyll, but on the back are 4 really Dr. Jekyll and 4 are instead Mr. Hyde.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These true identities remain unknown to the enemy until the characters are captured.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 3 different goals:&amp;#10;conquer the 4 Dr. Jekyll figures of the opponent&amp;#10;lose your own 4 Mr. Hyde figures&amp;#10;escape with your own Dr. Jekyll figure through an exit in a corner of the opposite side of the board&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How does the game start?&amp;#10;Each player takes 8 pieces of one color and then places them on the board as shown in Figure 1, with the names directed to the player and the unnamed part (or Dr. Jekyll) to the opponent. Place the pieces carefully so that the enemy does not see the true identity of the pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now you play alternately by moving one character forwards, backwards or sideways - never diagonally. If you move through a field occupied by the opponent, this figure is hit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win, one of the following conditions must be met:&amp;#10;conquer all 4 opposing Dr. Jekyll figures&amp;#10;lose all 4 of your own Mr. Hyde characters&amp;#10;leave with your own Dr. Jekyll figure in a corner on the opposite side of the field&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
